songs.embed_content: Read “Sleepless Eyes” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.title: Sleepless Eyes
songs.lyrics:
Know nothing of the world outside
Where we have never really been
Evening shows what morning hides
We sought out what cannot be seen

I have been so alone in your arms
Felt overflowing in your joy
Maybe you really meant no harm
Maybe you're just a weeping boy

I can't believe in your lie
And to the smoke of cigarettes
I still see your troubled eyes
You said it's easy to forget

The endless night is long behind
When I could never ever sleep
Yet somewhere far off in my mind
You haven't even ceased to weep

songs.embed_content: Read “Éblouis” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.title: Éblouis
songs.lyrics:
La lueur de l'est
Les longues ombres de l'aube
La poussière des pollens, des étés éblouis
Dans cette lumière, je disparais souvent

Éclats imprécis
D'une saison, d'une absence
Sous les arbres à l'abri
Nous voulions l'évidence
Nos heures endormies
Des instants sans distance
Dans les champs désunis
Et le jour qui avance

L'onde sur le lac
Les herbes dans le vent
Ton épaule et ma tempe
Le soleil et l'oubli
Dans la chaleur, tu m'appelais alors

Sous l'orage soudain
Nous ne voulions plus voir
Qu'une étendue sans fin
J'espère encore pouvoir
Nous deviner au loin
Dans la montée du soir
Les aiguilles des pins
Nous frôlaient dans le noir

Dernière nuit d'août
Aux pieds nus sur les pierres
La course hors d'haleine
Je ne quitterai jamais
Les éboulis et les points de côté

Nous suivions la rivière
Sous le ciel sans un bruit
Nous marchions solitaires
Et bientôt engourdis
Là où je nous perds
Deux formes indéfinies
Des blés laissés à terre
Et des feux dans la nuit

songs.embed_content: Read “April Come She Will” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.full_title: April Come She Will by Mohini Geisweiller
songs.title: April Come She Will

annotatable.link_title: April Come She Will by Mohini Geisweiller
annotatable.title: April Come She Will

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
April, come she will
When streams are ripe and swelled with rain
May, she will stay
Resting in my arms again

[Verse 2]
June, she’ll change her tune
In restless walks, she’ll prowl the night
July, she will fly
And give no warning to her flight

[Verse 3]
August, die she must
The autumn winds blow chilly and cold
September, I’ll remember
A love once new has now grown old

songs.embed_content: Read “Tempe” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.title: Tempe
songs.lyrics:
Une fin d'après-midi
Des ombres qui avancent
Le soir est si vite là
En septembre

Et le vent dans les arbres
Et la lumière d'été
Comme je voulais encore
Maintenant pas d'après

La chute d'un gobelet vide
Tout semble si normal
Et rien ne se passe
Rien ne m'arrivera jamais

Et le vent dans les arbres
Et la lumière d'été
Comme je voulais encore
Maintenant pas d'après

songs.embed_content: Read “Vale” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.title: Vale
songs.lyrics:
I'd like to come and go
I stand and stare
The clear plastic window
The single chair
Judging me by a picture, I get the things I asked for
And now I would stay here, you take me out

You take me in your car and close the door
I've been living this day before, as if I was
As they are, as a whole, a fold on waves
As they have a vale of tears to cross

There's someone living here but tell me who?
And every little help he's waiting for
Judging me by a picture, I get the things I asked for
And now I would stay here, you take me out

songs.embed_content: Read “Nightclubbers” by Mohini Geisweiller on Genius
songs.title: Nightclubbers
songs.lyrics:
Nightclubbers
For we've been dancing every night
Into the move of roving light
Random of my thought
Without a feeling
Into the same rim on and on

Cold glitters
You saw me sink into the dark
Into a flight of fallen sparks
Outside shone no sun
No wind was blowing
Long we have walked on broken gleams

Nightclubbers
For we've been dancing every night
More than once far, more than once tight
For we were awhile
Forever here
I'll always brush against your skin

Nightclubbers
I saw you die twice every night
I see you die twice every night
Wandering from my uncertain being
We sought oblivion

Nightclubbers
The fireflies fade in the dark
Unseen as fever
I see you dancing every night
Unseen forever
